      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Most do, but the implementation varies. Groq, OpenRouter, Together AI, and Fireworks AI all support the OpenAI-style tools parameter. Some smaller providers only support the older function_call parameter or skip tool use entirely. Always verify with a test call." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Which provider is best for production in 2026?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "For OpenAI-compatible production: Groq (if you can tolerate open models), Together AI (if you need fine-tuning), or OpenRouter (if you need model flexibility). For China production: FreeModel or apikey.fun. For data-sensitive workloads: self-hosted vLLM." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can I use the OpenAI Python SDK with these providers?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Set base_url to the provider's endpoint and the rest of your code works unchanged. Most providers' docs show the exact one-line change for OpenAI, Anthropic, and LlamaIndex SDKs." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is Anthropic Claude OpenAI-compatible?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "No. Claude uses a different API schema (Messages API, not Chat Completions). To use Claude through an OpenAI-compatible interface, route through OpenRouter or apikey.fun, which wrap Claude in OpenAI format. Direct Claude usage requires the anthropic SDK." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How does caching work across providers?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Anthropic pioneered prompt caching, OpenAI added it, and most OpenAI-compatible providers now support it. Cache reads are typically 50-90% cheaper than the standard input price. For long system prompts over 2K tokens, caching saves significant money. The implementation is provider-specific." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Which provider has the best free tier?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Groq. You get 1,000 requests per day, no credit card, no expiration. Most others cap at $1-10 in credits that expire in 30-90 days. Groq's free tier is genuinely useful for hobby projects and small production workloads." }
    }
  ]
